# Production deploy (Vercel)

Live app: **https://zebronics-master-tracker.vercel.app** (e.g. Rithika Amazon: `/app/ri/amazon`).

Git push to `main` alone does **not** update production unless Vercel Git integration or GitHub Actions ran. **Always deploy after pushing user-facing changes.**

## Required end-of-task steps

When the user asks to push, ship, or deploy—or when you finish UI/data fixes they will test on Vercel:

1. Commit and `git push origin main`
2. From repo root, run: `npm run deploy:prod`
3. Confirm deploy succeeds (alias `https://zebronics-master-tracker.vercel.app`)

If `deploy:prod` fails (not logged in), run `npx vercel login` once on the machine, then retry.

## Do not

- Stop after `git push` only and assume Vercel updated
- Skip deploy when only the user will verify on the production URL
